cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using a novel neural network architecture that can handle nested structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The paper also introduces a new neural network architecture, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of embeddings and contextual embeddings (BERT) suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision), which deal with image and text processing using neural networks.
